  <div class="info-box tip">
    <div class="box-title">📖 Key Takeaways</div>
    <p><strong>1. Impact first:</strong> A Collaborator ping is a medium; AWS credentials is a critical. Always push to demonstrate maximum impact before submitting.</p>
    <p><strong>2. Bypass everything:</strong> If the first payload is blocked, there are 50 more to try. Document what's blocked — it helps narrow down the filter type.</p>
    <p><strong>3. Deep dive the app:</strong> The best SSRF targets are in features you discover by actually using the application, not by automated scanners. Understand what each feature does server-side.</p>
    <p><strong>4. Second-order is undervalued:</strong> Most hunters test for immediate SSRF. Second-order SSRFs are found by fewer hunters and often have the same impact, but longer TTL to fix = more chance the company hasn't seen it.</p>
    <p><strong>5. Cloud = critical by default:</strong> Any SSRF in a cloud-hosted application that can reach 169.254.169.254 is automatically a critical finding if the metadata response is returned. No further exploitation needed to justify critical severity.</p>
